co-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg><span class=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">Sept 19, 2024</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104azl1665702554258.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/azl1665702554258.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/azl1665702554258.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"azl1665702554258\" role=\"article\">\n<h1 class=\"title topictitle1\" id=\"ariaid-title1\">\n      Indexed Lists\n </h1>\n<div class=\"body conbody\" id=\"azl1665702554258__indexed_lists_56268\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">In an indexed list, each list item can be referred to by a sequential number that identifies its position. The items are numbered starting with one.\n </p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"azl1665702554258__p_d16703e1_d16704e1_d16705e1\">For example, in the following list, the item in position 1 is <code class=\"ph codeph\">Monday</code>, in position 2 is <code class=\"ph codeph\">Tuesday</code>, and so on.</p>\n<div class=\"code-toolbar\"><pre class=\"pre language-plaintext\" tabindex=\"0\"><code class=\"language-plaintext\">\"Monday<span class=\"ph gold\">;</span>Tuesday<span class=\"ph gold\">;</span>Wednesday<span class=\"ph gold\">;</span>Thursday<span class=\"ph gold\">;</span>Friday<span class=\"ph gold\">;</span>Saturday<span class=\"ph gold\">;</span>Sunday\"</code></pre><div class=\"toolbar\"><div class=\"toolbar-item\"><button class=\"copy-to-clipboard-button\" data-copy-state=\"copy\" type=\"button\"><span>Copy</span></button></div></div></div>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"azl1665702554258__topic_d12102e1_d12103e1_d12104e1_d12105e1_d12106e1\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d996234e84\">\n                  \n Typed Lists\n </h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"azl1665702554258__p_d16709e1_d16710e1_d16711e1\">Uniface allows you to specify the data type of a list item. When used in ProcScript, the item value is then interpreted according to its data type. This is especially useful for sorting, because by default lists are sorted as strings. It is also useful when constructing a list of parameters to be passed with the <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">activate/list</span> command.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"azl1665702554258__p_d16712e1_d16713e1_d16714e1\">To explicitly specify the type as Boolean, Float, or String, use the <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">$typed</span> function. For other data types and syntax strings, you can use a data type ProcScript function.</p>\n<div class=\"table-wrap\"><table class=\"table\" count-columns=\"3\" id=\"azl1665702554258__table_d1790e1_d1791e1_d1792e1\"><caption><span class=\"table--title-label\">Table 1. </span><span class=\"title\">Data Type Conversion Functions</span></caption><colgroup><col/><col/><col/></colgroup><thead class=\"thead\">\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<th class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" id=\"azl1665702554258__table_d1790e1_d1791e1_d1792e1__entry__1\">Using <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">$typed</span>\n</th>\n<th class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" id=\"azl1665702554258__table_d1790e1_d1791e1_d1792e1__entry__2\">Type-specific ProcScript Function</th>\n<th class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" id=\"azl1665702554258__table_d1790e1_d1791e1_d1792e1__entry__3\">Returns</th>\n</tr>\n</thead><tbody class=\"tbody\">\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"azl1665702554258__table_d1790e1_d1791e1_d1792e1__entry__1\"><span class=\"keyword cmdname\">$typed</span>\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">(\"$boolean(</code>\n<var class=\"keyword varname\">Value</var><code class=\"ph codeph\">)\")</code>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"azl1665702554258__table_d1790e1_d1791e1_d1792e1__entry__2\"></td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"azl1665702554258__table_d1790e1_d1791e1_d1792e1__entry__3\">Boolean </td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"azl1665702554258__table_d1790e1_d1791e1_d1792e1__entry__1\"><span class=\"keyword cmdname\">$typed</span>\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">(\"$clock(</code>\n<var class=\"keyword varname\">Value</var>\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">)\")</code>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"azl1665702554258__table_d1790e1_d1791e1_d1792e1__entry__2\">\n<code class=\"ph codeph\"><a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"kbw1665702554427.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/kbw1665702554427.html\" title=\"Return the system time or convert the argument to the Time data type.\">$clock</a>(</code>\n<var class=\"keyword varname\">Value</var>\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">)</code>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"azl1665702554258__table_d1790e1_d1791e1_d1792e1__entry__3\">Time type </td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"azl1665702554258__table_d1790e1_d1791e1_d1792e1__entry__1\"><span class=\"keyword cmdname\">$typed</span>\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">(\"$date(</code>\n<var class=\"keyword varname\">Value</var>\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">)\")</code>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"azl1665702554258__table_d1790e1_d1791e1_d1792e1__entry__2\">\n<code class=\"ph codeph\"><a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"qdt1718972098664.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/qdt1718972098664.html\" title=\"Return the current date or convert the argument to the Date data type.\">$date</a>(</code>\n<var class=\"keyword varname\">Value</var>\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">)</code>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"azl1665702554258__table_d1790e1_d1791e1_d1792e1__entry__3\">Date type </td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"azl1665702554258__table_d1790e1_d1791e1_d1792e1__entry__1\"><span class=\"keyword cmdname\">$typed</span>\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">(\"$datim(</code>\n<var class=\"keyword varname\">Value</var>\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">)\")</code>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"azl1665702554258__table_d1790e1_d1791e1_d1792e1__entry__2\">\n<code class=\"ph codeph\"><a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"wvg1665702554514.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/wvg1665702554514.html\" title=\"Return the system date and time, or convert the argument to the Datetime data type.\">$datim</a>(</code>\n<var class=\"keyword varname\">Value</var>\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">)</code>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"azl1665702554258__table_d1790e1_d1791e1_d1792e1__entry__3\">DateTime type </td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"azl1665702554258__table_d1790e1_d1791e1_d1792e1__entry__1\"><span class=\"keyword cmdname\">$typed</span>\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">(\"$float(</code>\n<var class=\"keyword varname\">Value</var>\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">)\")</code>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"azl1665702554258__table_d1790e1_d1791e1_d1792e1__entry__2\"></td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"azl1665702554258__table_d1790e1_d1791e1_d1792e1__entry__3\">Float type</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"azl1665702554258__table_d1790e1_d1791e1_d1792e1__entry__1\"><span class=\"keyword cmdname\">$typed</span>\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">(\"$number(</code>\n<var class=\"keyword varname\">Value</var>\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">)\")</code>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"azl1665702554258__table_d1790e1_d1791e1_d1792e1__entry__2\">\n<code class=\"ph codeph\"><a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"mfg1718973151470.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/mfg1718973151470.html\" title=\"Returns a numeric value derived from a numeric string.\">$number</a>(</code>\n<var class=\"keyword varname\">Value</var>\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">)</code>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"azl1665702554258__table_d1790e1_d1791e1_d1792e1__entry__3\">Number type</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"azl1665702554258__table_d1790e1_d1791e1_d1792e1__entry__1\"><span class=\"keyword cmdname\">$typed</span>\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">(\"$string(</code>\n<var class=\"keyword varname\">Value</var>\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">)\")</code>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"azl1665702554258__table_d1790e1_d1791e1_d1792e1__entry__2\">Although there is a\n\t\t\t\t <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">$string</span> ProcScript function, it is used to convert XML entities to strings, not\n\t\t\t\t to convert data to String.</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"azl1665702554258__table_d1790e1_d1791e1_d1792e1__entry__3\">Constant string type</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"azl1665702554258__table_d1790e1_d1791e1_d1792e1__entry__1\"><span class=\"keyword cmdname\">$typed</span>\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">(\"$syntax(</code>\n<var class=\"keyword varname\">Value</var>\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">)\")</code>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"azl1665702554258__table_d1790e1_d1791e1_d1792e1__entry__2\">\n<code class=\"ph codeph\"><a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"bqr1665702555238.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/bqr1665702555238.html\" title=\"Convert a string to a syntax string.\">$syntax</a>(</code>\n<var class=\"keyword varname\">Value</var>\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">)</code>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"azl1665702554258__table_d1790e1_d1791e1_d1792e1__entry__3\">Syntax string type</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\">\n<td class=\"entry\" headers=\"azl1665702554258__table_d1790e1_d1791e1_d1792e1__entry__1\"><code class=\"ph codeph\">$typed</code><code class=\"ph codeph\">(\"$regex(</code><var class=\"keyword varname\">Value</var><code class=\"ph codeph\">)\")</code></td>\n<td class=\"entry\" headers=\"azl1665702554258__table_d1790e1_d1791e1_d1792e1__entry__2\"><code class=\"ph codeph\"><a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"tqa1714484099568.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/tqa1714484099568.html\" title=\"Convert a string to a regex string.\">$regex</a>(</code><var class=\"keyword varname\">Value</var><code class=\"ph codeph\">)</code></td>\n<td class=\"entry\" headers=\"azl1665702554258__table_d1790e1_d1791e1_d1792e1__entry__3\">Regex string type</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody></table></div>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"azl1665702554258__section_w1y_dgx_tcc\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d996234e428\">Example: Typed List</h2>\n<div class=\"div\">\n<p class=\"p\">For example, the following code generates a list with different values\n               for <code class=\"ph codeph\">012345</code> depending on the data type:</p>\n<div class=\"code-toolbar\"><pre class=\"pre language-plaintext\" id=\"azl1665702554258__pre_elg_hgx_tcc\" tabindex=\"0\"><code class=\"language-plaintext\">variables\n string vList\nendvariables\nputitem vList, -1, $typed(\"$string(012345)\")\nputitem vList, -1, $typed(\"$boolean(012345)\") ; start with 0 yields F\nputitem vList, -1, $typed(\"$boolean(12345)\") ; start with any other character yields T\nputitem vList, -1, $typed(\"$float(012345)\")\nputitem vList, -1, $number(012345)\nputitem vList, -1, $date(12-3-45) ; requires valid input string\nputitem vList, -1, $clock(012345)\n;Result: vList = 012345<span class=\"ph gold\">;</span>F<span class=\"ph gold\">;</span>T<span class=\"ph gold\">;</span>12345<span class=\"ph gold\">;</span>12345<span class=\"ph gold\">;</span>20450312<span class=\"ph gold\">;</span>0000000001234500</code></pre><div class=\"toolbar\"><div class=\"toolbar-item\"><button class=\"copy-to-clipboard-button\" data-copy-state=\"copy\" type=\"button\"><span>Copy</span></button></div></div></div>\n</div>\n</section>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div><div class=\"contentPlaceholder\" style=\"height: 500px;\"><div class=\"contentContainer zDocsSideBoxes\"><div><h5 aria-level=\"5\" class=\"css-g931ng\">Related Links</h5><ul><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/ayl1665702554178.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>Lists and Sublists</a><p>A list is a group of related items homogeneous items collected into a single unit, the list. Every item in a list is assumed to have the same structure.</p></li><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/vkk1665702553651.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>Sorting Data in ProcScript</a><p>Uniface provides ProcScript instructions for sorting entity occurrences in hitlists and lists created in ProcScript. It is possible to perform multi-level sorting, enabling you to sort by several fields, each with its own sort criteria.</p></li><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/iyj1665702557441.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>$typed</a><p>Explicitly convert data to a specified data type.</p></li><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/fxx1665702529732.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>activate</a><p>Calls an operation on a component instance.</p></li></ul></div></div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2525935\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2525935\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "Indexed Lists Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Sept 19, 2024 Summarize Uniface 10.4 Indexed Lists In an indexed list, each list item can be referred to by a sequential number that identifies its position. The items are numbered starting with one. For example, in the following list, the item in position 1 is Monday , in position 2 is Tuesday , and so on. \"Monday ; Tuesday ; Wednesday ; Thursday ; Friday ; Saturday ; Sunday\" Copy Typed Lists Uniface allows you to specify the data type of a list item. When used in ProcScript, the item value is then interpreted according to its data type. This is especially useful for sorting, because by default lists are sorted as strings. It is also useful when constructing a list of parameters to be passed with the activate/list command. To explicitly specify the type as Boolean, Float, or String, use the $typed function. For other data types and syntax strings, you can use a data type ProcScript function. Table 1. Data Type Conversion Functions Using $typed Type-specific ProcScript Function Returns $typed (\"$boolean( Value )\") Boolean $typed (\"$clock( Value )\") $clock ( Value ) Time type $typed (\"$date( Value )\") $date ( Value ) Date type $typed (\"$datim( Value )\") $datim ( Value ) DateTime type $typed (\"$float( Value )\") Float type $typed (\"$number( Value )\") $number ( Value ) Number type $typed (\"$string( Value )\") Although there is a $string ProcScript function, it is used to convert XML entities to strings, not to convert data to String. Constant string type $typed (\"$syntax( Value )\") $syntax ( Value ) Syntax string type $typed (\"$regex( Value )\") $regex ( Value ) Regex string type Example: Typed List For example, the following code generates a list with different values for 012345 depending on the data type: variables string vList endvariables putitem vList, -1, $typed(\"$string(012345)\") putitem vList, -1, $typed(\"$boolean(012345)\") ; start with 0 yields F putitem vList, -1, $typed(\"$boolean(12345)\") ; start with any other character yields T putitem vList, -1, $typed(\"$float(012345)\") putitem vList, -1, $number(012345) putitem vList, -1, $date(12-3-45) ; requires valid input string putitem vList, -1, $clock(012345) ;Result: vList = 012345 ; F ; T ; 12345 ; 12345 ; 20450312 ; 0000000001234500 Copy Related Links Lists and Sublists A list is a group of related items homogeneous items collected into a single unit, the list. Every item in a list is assumed to have the same structure. Sorting Data in ProcScript Uniface provides ProcScript instructions for sorting entity occurrences in hitlists and lists created in ProcScript. It is possible to perform multi-level sorting, enabling you to sort by several fields, each with its own sort criteria. $typed Explicitly convert data to a specified data type. activate Calls an operation on a component instance. Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}